	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64367610"><p>Microsoft should be thrilled about the prospect of being able to fix safety defects at distribute those fixes electronically at low cost to themselves.  Instead they've chosen to monetized their own failures and incompetence by charging people for the privilege of having the vendor correct their own safety defects.  This practice is disgusting and (should be) illegal.</p></div>
